{
  "text": "It is of great importance that the phenotypic variation (σ̂ 2 p ) be composed, for the most part, of variations from the genotype of the selection candidates, since it contributes to higher heritability of the trait in question. We highlight the high phenotypic variation of the WTS and NSI traits, basically composed by the variation of the genotype (Table  1) . According to [CITATION_1] , WTS and NSI were the most efficient (largest relative contribution) in explaining genetic variability among P. plicatulum × P. lepton hybrids, showing the importance of these variables as a component in the production of seeds and, possibly in the selection of superior genotypes.",
  "correct_citation": {
